==Old English==
===Etymology===
Common Germanic *''[[fimfi]]'' from Indo-European ''*penkwe'' ‘five’. Cognates include Old High German ''fimf'', ''finf'' (German ''[[fünf]]''), Old Saxon ''fīf'' (Dutch [[vijf]]), Old Norse ''[[fimm]]'' (Swedish ''[[fem]]''), Gothic [[𐍆𐌹𐌼𐍆]].  The IE root is also the source of Greek ''[[πέντε]]'', Latin ''[[quinque]]'', Sanskrit [[पञ्चन्]].

